The Puppet keyword used to extend the functionality of a class is called:

extend
declare
--inherits
include
Correct!

When the derived (inherited) class is declared, its base class is automatically declared first.

--True
False
Correct.


You have a base class called `ssh` that you need to extend. The new class will be called `ssh::paranoid`. Which of the following is the correct syntax for the first line of the `paranoid` class? (Multiple answers are allowed.)

class paranoid extends ssh {
class paranoid inherits ssh {
class ssh declares paranoid {
--class ssh::paranoid inherits ssh {
Correct!


Inheritance should be used within a module to reduce repetition.

